Janet's ducks lay 16 eggs per day. She eats 3 eggs for breakfast and uses 4 eggs to bake muffins. The total number of eggs used for breakfast and muffins is:

$$
3 \text{ (breakfast)} + 4 \text{ (muffins)} = 7 \text{ eggs}
$$

The remainder of eggs sold at the market is:

$$
16 \text{ (total eggs)} - 7 \text{ (used eggs)} = 9 \text{ eggs}
$$

Each egg is sold for $2, so the total revenue from the market is:

$$
9 \text{ eggs} \times 2 \text{ dollars/egg} = 18 \text{ dollars}
$$

