Janet's ducks lay 16 eggs per day. She uses 3 eggs for breakfast and 4 eggs to bake muffins. The total number of eggs used daily is:

$$
3 \text{ (breakfast)} + 4 \text{ (muffins)} = 7 \text{ eggs}
$$

The remaining eggs for sale are:

$$
16 \text{ (total eggs)} - 7 \text{ (used eggs)} = 9 \text{ eggs}
$$

She sells these 9 eggs at $2 per egg:

$$
9 \text{ eggs} \times \$2/\text{egg} = \$18
$$

